cally%20conducts%20hunts%20in%20some%20parks%20to%20keep%20the%20deer%20population%20under%20control.%20%26quot%3BUntil%20this%20year%2C%20all%20results%20for%20these%20parks%20had%20been%20negative%20(for%20CWD)%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20press%20release%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%C2%A0Zombie%20Deer%20Disease%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChronic%20wasting%20disease%2C%20also%20known%20as%20'zombie%20deer%20disease'%2C%20is%20the%20illness%20that%20leaves%20animals%20confused%20and%20drooling%2C%20It%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffirst-case-of-zombie-deer-disease-found-in-us-yellowstone-park-know-what-it-is-4589381%5C%22%3Efirst%20detected%20in%C2%A0Yellowstone%20National%20Park%20in%20November%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0last%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20disease%20is%20caused%20by%20misfolded%20proteins%20-%20when%20proteins%20do%20not%20fold%20into%20the%20correct%20shape%20-%20known%20as%20prions.%20After%20infection%2C%20prions%20travel%20throughout%20the%20central%20nervous%20system%2C%20leaving%20prion%20deposits%20in%20brain%20tissues%20and%20organs.%20The%20deer%20affected%20by%20it%20are%20left%20drooling%2C%20stumbling%2C%20lethargic%20and%20with%20a%20blank%20stare%2C%20due%20to%20which%20the%20infection%20has%20been%20given%20the%20name%20%26quot%3Bzombie%20deer%20disease%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%2C%20it%20may%20take%20over%20a%20year%20for%20symptoms%20in%20the%20deer%20to%20develop.%20It%20usually%20starts%20with%20the%20deer%20drastically%20losing%20weight%2C%20stumbling%20around%2C%20and%20losing%20all%20energy.%C2%A0At%20present%2C%20CWD%20does%20not%20have%20any%20cure%20or%20vaccine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20known%20case%20of%20CWD%20in%20humans%20has%20ever%20been%20recorded%2C%20according%20to%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20data-id%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxnews.com%2Fus%2Fzombie-deer-disease-concerns-scientists-possible-spread-humans%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22URL%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxnews.com%2Fus%2Fzombie-deer-disease-concerns-scientists-possible-spread-humans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFox%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0However%2C%20some%20studies%20have%20suggested%20chronic%20wasting%20disease%20is%20a%20risk%20to%20monkeys%20that%20eat%20infected%20animal%20meat%20or%20come%20in%20contact%20with%20infected%20animal%20brains%20or%20bodily%20fluids.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20have%20labelled%20CWD%20as%20a%20''slow-moving%20disaster''%20and%20are%20strongly%20advising%20governments%20to%20prepare%20for%20the%20likelihood%20of%20its%20transmission%20to%20humans.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714024080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fbmv6l7n8_deer_625x300_25_April_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fzombie-deer-disease-hits-another-us-state-as-2-white-tailed-deers-test-positive-in-virginia-5518398%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chronic%20wasting%20disease%2C%20also%20known%20as%20'zombie%20deer%20disease'%2C%20is%20the%20illness%20that%20leaves%20animals%20confused%20and%20drooling.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fzombie-deer-disease-hits-another-us-state-as-2-white-tailed-deers-test-positive-in-virginia-5518398%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fzombie-deer-disease-hits-another-us-state-as-2-white-tailed-deers-test-positive-in-virginia-5518398%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fzombie-deer-disease-hits-another-us-state-as-2-white-tailed-deers-test-positive-in-virginia-5518398%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22This%20Alia-Neetu%2C%20Soni%20Razdan%20Red%20Carpet%20Mom