0idea%20of%20work%20travel%2C%20I%20enjoy%20it.%20I%20love%20checking%20into%20a%20hotel%2C%20going%20to%20the%20gym%20or%20taking%20a%20dip%20in%20the%20pool%2C%20grabbing%20a%20local%20coffee%20on%20my%20way%20to%20work%2C%20going%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalking-meetings-health-benefits-sitting-more-focused-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewalking%20meetings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20exploring%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20is%20also%20an%20enthusiastic%20traveler%2C%20and%20together%2C%20we%20have%20explored%20the%20world%20far%20and%20wide.%20Since%20my%20son%20was%20born%2C%20we've%20focused%20on%20getting%20him%20used%20to%20traveling.%20We%20took%20him%20on%20a%2010-hour%20flight%20when%20he%20was%204%20months%20old%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2019%2F12%2F20%2Fhow-to-fly-with-baby-on-an-airplane.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etook%2030%20flights%20before%20he%20turned%202%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20have%20taken%20him%20to%20nearly%2020%20countries.%20It's%20already%20clear%20that%20the%20travel%20bug%20has%20bitten%20him%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20traveling%20with%20children%20is%20fun%2C%20I%20missed%20the%20spontaneity%20and%20the%20flexibility%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feurope-solo-travel-woman-burnout-phd-academic-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolo%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20can%20stay%20wherever%20you%20want%2C%20eat%20what%20you%20like%2C%20and%20explore%20the%20city%20without%20worrying%20about%20pushing%20a%20stroller%2C%20managing%20bedtimes%2C%20or%20keeping%20a%20close%20watch%20on%20your%20child%20in%20an%20overcrowded%20area.%20I%20also%20loved%20how%20I%20could%20sleep%20past%206%20a.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20packed%20working-parent%20schedule%20doesn't%20allow%20for%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-30s-best-time-to-solo-travel-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolo%20travel%20%3C%2Fa%3Eopportunities%2C%20but%20work%20trips%20are%20my%20way%20of%20relishing%20in%20something%20I%20enjoy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMoms%20need%20to%20stop%20feeling%20guilty%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-caregiver-father-distance-working-mom-guilt-shame-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorking%20moms%20have%20long%20suffered%20the%20guilt%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20not%20being%20able%20to%20spend%20enough%20time%20with%20their%20children.%20A%20study%20conducted%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F36097879%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGender%2520stereotypes%2520prescribe%2520mothers%252C%2520but%2Ctheir%2520work%2520over%2520their%2520family.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBritish%20Psychological%20Society%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%20found%20that%20gender%20stereotypes%20can%20predict%20the%20levels%20of%20guilt%20that%20working%20parents%20feel%2C%20with%20working%20mothers%20feeling%20higher%20levels%20of%20guilt%20compared%20to%20working%20fathers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20study%2C%20conducted%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2015%2F04%2F01%2Fworking-mom-guilt-many-dads-feel-it-too%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20in%202015%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20showed%20that%20children's%20academic%20and%20emotional%20well-being%20is%20not%20contingent%20on%20the%20time%20they%20spend%20with%20their%20mothers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20working%20parent%20who%20loves%20to%20travel%2C%20the%20feeling%20is%20all%20too%20familiar.%20The%20guilt%20gets%20exacerbated%20when%20friends%20and%20family%20often%20look%20at%20me%20with%20surprise%20and%20ask%20how%20my%20child%20is%20managing%20without%20me.%20No%20one%20asks%20me%20that%20question%20when%20my%20husband%20is%20away%20on%20business%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that's%20another%20conversation%20for%20another%20essay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20decided%20to%20give%20my%20guilt%20structure%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20adding%20more%20extra%20days%20on%20business%20trips%2C%20I%20realized%20how%20liberating%20it%20was%20to%20travel%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-every-working-mom-take-strategic-vacation-alone-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20first%20tried%20solo%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20planning%20a%20business%20trip%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20After%20a%20week%20of%20meetings%20in%20New%20York%2C%20I%20stayed%20for%20an%20extra%20night%20and%20treated%20myself%20to%20a%20glass%20of%20wine%20at%20the%20One%20World%20Observatory%20in%20downtown%20Manhattan.%20I%20just%20sat%20there%2C%20swirling%20my%20glass%20and%20watching%20the%20world%20go%20by.%20The%20sense%20of%20calmness%20was%20a%20feeling%20I%20rarely%20find%20as%20a%20working%20mom%2C%20and%20I%20loved%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20I've%20stopped%20by%20the%20Great%20Wall%20on%20a%20trip%20to%20China%2C%20popped%20into%20the%20Metropolitan%20Museum%20of%20Art%20in%20New%20York%2C%20and%20spent%20a%20weekend%20exploring%20Angkor%20Wat%2C%20a%20temple%20in%20Cambodia%2C%20after%20a%20week%20of%20meetings%20in%20Singapore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20learned%20to%20handle%20and%20even%20bounce%20back%20from%20my%20mom%20guilt%20spirals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20standing%20in%20winter%20clothes%20holding%20a%20coffee%20in%20New%20York%20City%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662738360dfb1341e9fdd121%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22576%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhen%20guilt%20gets%20the%20best%20of%20her%2C%20the%20author%20will%20go%20for%20a%20short%20walk%20to%20clear%20her%20head.%20%3Cp%3ESpriha%20Srivastava%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20steps%20that%20helped%20me%20deal%20with%20the%20guilt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20%3Cstrong%3ELean%20on%20your%20partner%20or%20family%20for%20support%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can't%20help%20but%20think%20of%20the%20phrase%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-moms-tiktok-parenting-trends-it-takes-village-raise-children-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BIt%20takes%20a%20village%20to%20raise%20a%20child.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20It%20does.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELean%20on%20your%20partner%20%E2%80%94%20or%20friends%20and%20family%20%E2%80%94%20for%20support%20while%20you%20are%20away.%20They%20can%20help%20you%20stay%20connected%20with%20your%20children%2C%20reason%20if%20your%20child%20is%20upset%2C%20and%20help%20you%20be%20an%20important%20part%20of%20your%20child's%20schedule%20even%20when%20you%20are%20in%20a%20different%20time%20zone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20%3Cstrong%3ETalk%20about%20your%20travel%20with%20your%20child%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELet%20your%20child%20know%20how%20excited%20you%20are%20about%20an%20adventure.%20Before%20you%20hop%20on%20the%20plane%2C%20show%20them%20pictures%20or%20YouTube%20videos%20of%20where%20you%20are%20traveling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%20knows%20how%20much%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20love%20traveling%20and%20is%20very%20engaged%20when%20I%20talk%20to%20him%20ahead%20of%20a%20solo%20trip.%20We%20talk%20about%20the%20city%2C%20the%20stories%20behind%20it%2C%20the%20food%2C%20and%20the%20people%20%E2%80%94%20and%20he%20even%20requests%20what%20souvenirs%20to%20bring%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20before%20my%20trip%20to%20China%20last%20year%2C%20my%20son%20and%20I%20discussed%20the%20Great%20Wall%20and%20how%20it%20was%20built.%20He%20was%20fascinated%20and%20asked%20me%20to%20send%20him%20pictures%20throughout%20the%20trip%2C%20which%20helped%20ease%20my%20guilt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20%3Cstrong%3EFollow%20your%20child's%20schedule%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20that%20my%20son%20feels%20more%20confident%20and%20comfortable%20when%20his%20day%20is%20predictable%20and%20familiar.%20Ensure%20that%20whoever%20is%20looking%20after%20your%20child%20follows%20their%20set%20routine%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftoo-many-days-off-school-student-learning-loss-parent-stress-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildren%20thrive%20in%20a%20routine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIdentify%20the%20times%20during%20the%20day%20when%20they%20need%20you%20the%20most%20and%20plug%20into%20their%20daily%20routine%20with%20Facetime%20and%20video%20calls.%20It%20may%20not%20be%20the%20same%20as%20being%20there%20in%20person%2C%20but%20it%20likely%20makes%20them%20feel%20comfortable%20knowing%20you're%20just%20a%20phone%20call%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETime%20zones%20can%20make%20coordinating%20schedules%20tricky%20%E2%80%94%20bedtime%20can%20come%20when%20I'm%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20meeting%20%E2%80%94%20so%20I%20schedule%20voice%20notes%2C%20pictures%2C%20and%20videos.%20I'll%20even%20send%20my%20husband%20detailed%20voice%20notes%20to%20play%20to%20our%20son%20before%20he%20goes%20to%20sleep.%20The%20bonus%20is%20I%20wake%20up%20to%20some%20adorable%20voice%20notes%20that%20are%20a%20great%20start%20to%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20%3Cstrong%3EWalk%20the%20guilt%20away%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20doing%20all%20of%20the%20above%2C%20the%20guilt%20still%20sneaks%20in%20occasionally.%20So%20I%20immediately%20go%20out%20for%20a%20quick%20walk%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilent-walk-hot-girl-trend-older-generation-millennials-zoomers-annoyed-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20clear%20my%20head%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remind%20myself%20this%20may%20feel%20tough%2C%20but%20I%20am%20teaching%20my%20son%20the%20importance%20of%20leaning%20into%20your%20interests%20and%20passions.%20I%20am%20also%20teaching%20him%20that%20his%20parents%20may%20travel%20for%20work%2C%20but%20he'll%20always%20have%20a%20support%20system%20back%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20easy%2C%20and%20sometimes%20it%20feels%20like%20moving%20mountains%2C%20but%20the%20thrill%20of%20exploring%20a%20new%20place%20and%20the%20tiny%20cuddles%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20trip%20make%20the%20journey%20worthwhile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-mom-solo-travel-mom-guilt-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714004041000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66272de723b29110d301ae51%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-mom-solo-travel-mom-guilt-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20a%20working%20parent%2C%20Spriha%20Srivastava%20often%20has%20mom%20guilt%20when%20traveling.%20She%20now%20enjoys%20trips%20after%20dealing%20ways%20to%20deal%20with%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ssrivastava%40businessinsider.com%20(Spriha%20Srivastava)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-mom-solo-travel-mom-guilt-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mark%20Zuckerberg%20laid%20out%203%20ways%20Meta%20will%20make%20money%20from%20its%20huge%20AI%20investments%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Meta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6629966223b29110d302cbd3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMeta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%3Cp%3EBrendan%20Smilalowski%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%2C%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%20has%20recently%20become%20%26quot%3Bmore%20ambitious%26quot%3B%20about%20Meta's%20ability%20to%20win%20in%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20now%20plans%20to%20spend%20around%20%2440%20billion%20this%20year%2C%20largely%20on%20AI%20investments.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20Zuckerberg%20sees%20three%20ways%20AI%20can%20become%20a%20%26quot%3Bmassive%20business%26quot%3B%20for%20Meta.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-did-not-see-the-genai-wave-coming-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20now%20convinced%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-considered-paying-users-for-data-lawsuit-reveals-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20top%20AI%20company%2C%20and%20he%20even%20knows%20how%20the%20technology%20will%20become%20a%20significant%20source%20of%20profit%20in%20the%20years%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20recent%20release%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-llama-3-chatbot-mark-zuckerberg-existential-risks-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELlama%203%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Meta's%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-can-ingest-books-data-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20model%2C%20Zuckerberg%20said%20he%20became%20%26quot%3Bmore%20ambitious%20and%20optimistic%20on%20AI%26quot%3B%20and%20his%20company's%20ability%20to%20deliver%20on%20the%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20made%20it%20clear%20during%20a%20Wednesday%20earnings%20call%20with%20analysts%20that%20he%20intends%20to%20%26quot%3Binvest%20significantly%20more%20over%20the%20coming%20years%20to%20build%20even%20more%20advanced%20models%20and%20the%20largest%20scale%20AI%20services%20in%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20latest%20models%2C%20we're%20not%20just%20building%20good%20AI%20models%20that%20are%20capable%20of%20building%20some%20new%20good%20social%20and%20commerce%20products%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CEO%20told%20analysts.%20%26quot%3BI%20actually%20think%20we're%20in%20a%20place%20where%20we've%20shown%20that%20we%20can%20build%20leading%20models%20and%20be%20the%20leading%20AI%20company%20in%20the%20world.%20And%20that%20opens%20up%20a%20lot%20of%20additional%20opportunities%20beyond%20just%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20the%20most%20obvious%20for%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHeavy%20spending%20again%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20ambition%20does%20not%20come%20cheap.%20Meta%20increased%20its%20guidance%20on%20capital%20expenditure%20for%20this%20year%2C%20saying%20it%20now%20plans%20to%20spend%20between%20%2435%20billion%20and%20%2440%20billion%2C%20largely%20on%20AI%20investments.%20Its%20stock%20slumped%2016%25%20in%20after-hours%20trading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20time%20Zuckerberg%20got%20excited%20about%20a%20new%20technology%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fmeta-facebook-share-price-mark-zuckerberg-metaverse-dream-earnings-2022-10%3F_gl%3D1*1x7y01m*_ga*NzEzMjQwNDM2LjE2OTU3NDY5MDM.*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTcxMzk5ODQ2My4yMTYuMS4xNzEzOTk4NDc4LjQ1LjAuMA..%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20metaverse%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20Meta%20spent%20wildly%20and%20freaked%20investors%20out.%20The%20stock%20collapsed%20and%20didn't%20recover%20until%20the%20company%20embarked%20on%20a%20%26quot%3BYear%20of%20Efficiency%26quot%3B%20marked%20by%20mass%20layoffs%20and%20a%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-mark-zuckerberg-meta-facebook-ceo-layoffs-profit-cage-match-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebusiness-minded%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20on%20Wednesday%20made%20a%20concerted%20effort%20to%20head%20off%20Wall%20Street%20panic%20that%20his%20new%20AI%20enthusiasm%20is%20lacking%20in%20business%20acumen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20sees%20%26quot%3Bseveral%20ways%26quot%3B%20generative%20AI%20can%20make%20money%2C%20and%20laid%20out%20three%20specific%20paths%20to%20this%20becoming%20%26quot%3Ba%20massive%20business%26quot%3B%20for%20Meta.%20Although%20getting%20there%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Blong-term%26quot%3B%20prospect%2C%20he%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%26quot%3BBusiness%20messaging%26quot%3B%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20ways%20AI%20can%20make%20money%20is%20by%20building%20up%20%26quot%3Bbusiness%20messaging%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20companies%20pay%20Meta%20for%20generative%20AI%20tools%2C%20such%20as%20services%20that%20support%20automated%20interactions%20with%20users%20and%20customers.%20Zuckerberg%20envisions%20Meta's%20AI%20moving%20beyond%20just%20being%20a%20chatbot%20and%20becoming%20an%20AI%20%26quot%3Bagent%26quot%3B%20that%20handles%20more%20complex%20tasks%2C%20and%20processes%20multiple%20queries%20to%20solve%20user%20problems%2C%20instead%20of%20coming%20back%20instantly%20with%20rote%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERevenue%20from%20AI%20business%20messaging%20is%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20nearer%20term%20opportunities%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said.%20While%20it%20may%20not%20become%20a%20reality%20this%20year%2C%20he%20noted%20that%20it's%20less%20than%20five%20years%20away.%20The%20immediate%20goal%20on%20this%20front%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bget%20many%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20or%20billions%20of%20people%20to%20use%20Meta%20AI%20as%20a%20core%20part%20of%20what%20they%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAds%20appearing%20in%20%26quot%3BAI%20interactions%26quot%3B%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20way%20generative%20AI%20could%20make%20money%20for%20Meta%20is%20by%20%26quot%3Bintroducing%20ads%20or%20paid%20content%20into%20AI%20interactions%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said.%20Although%20brands%20and%20companies%20paying%20for%20products%20to%20show%20up%20in%20generative%20AI%20results%20is%20not%20yet%20the%20standard%20for%20AI%20chatbots%2C%20Meta's%20entire%20business%20is%20effectively%20driven%20by%20selling%20digital%20advertising.%20Inserting%20ads%20into%20its%20social%20and%20messaging%20products%20is%20at%20the%20core%20of%20Meta%20as%20a%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20is%20already%20being%20more%20widely%20deployed%20by%20Meta%20in%20its%20newer%20%26quot%3Bunconnected%20content%26quot%3B%20algorithm%20for%20social%20content%20recommendations%2C%20which%20Zuckerberg%20said%20is%20leading%20to%20more%20app%20engagement.%20That%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20leads%20to%20more%20people%20seeing%20more%20ads.%20Right%20now%2C%2030%25%20of%20the%20content%20Facebook%20users%20see%20is%20recommended%20by%20AI%2C%20and%20the%20same%20goes%20for%2050%25%20of%20the%20content%20seen%20by%20Instagram%20users%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESelling%20access%20to%20AI%20models%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20third%20distinct%20way%20Meta%20may%20make%20money%20from%20AI%20is%20by%20selling%20access%20to%20models%20as%20they%20get%20larger.%20%26quot%3BEnabling%20people%20to%20pay%20to%20use%20bigger%20AI%20models%20and%20access%20more%20compute%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Zuckerberg%20put%20it%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20Llama%203%20and%20the%20Meta's%20other%20large%20language%20models%20are%20freely%20available%20to%20users%20and%20companies%20below%20a%20certain%20size%20threshold.%20Charging%20for%20access%20might%20be%20a%20move%20away%20from%20Meta's%20%26quot%3Bopen%20source%26quot%3B%20approach%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20if%20the%20technology%20and%20products%20evolve%20in%20the%20way%20that%20we%20hope%2C%20each%20of%20those%20will%20unlock%20massive%20amounts%20of%20value%20for%20people%20and%20business%20for%20us%20over%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20makes%20sense%20to%20go%20for%20it%2C%20and%20we're%20going%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-plan-meta-make-money-from-ai-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714003589000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6629936b0dfb1341e9feebc3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A